Intrinsic - Intrinsic Experts Who We Are Meet our Experts Blog Talk to an Expert TALKÂ TOÂ ANÂ EXPERT TALKÂ TOÂ ANÂ EXPERT Meet Our Experts Our network of brand builders, consumer health experts and entrepreneurs share how they help health and wellness founders achieve their mission Mehmet Oz Host, The Oz Show Oz discusses why he joined Intrinsic as an investor and strategic advisor - and how he can help your health and wellness brand reach a larger READ THE FULL INTERVIEW Tell us your I m Mehmet Iâm a surgeon, TV host, and an entrepreneur, as well as an investor in, and strategic advisor to, What do you look for in a health and wellness brand? This is what I look for in a health and wellness I want it to be I want it to be innovative and improve on the status I want to address an issue that s big that a large population can benefit And I want it to be accessible and affordable for most people, so we can democratize Why did you decide to work with Intrinsic? I m working with Intrinsic because I am passionate about entrepreneurship, and I know how difficult it can be when you feel like you re the only one out there - and what you want is a partner, someone you can I decided to work with Intrinsic because I know they share my mission, which is to help people achieve better They are real experts, not only in brand building and , but in health - what I really care And they are helping the They are working with small brands and What is your message for health and wellness founders? My message for health and wellness founders is that I know how hard you worked to give birth to this I want to help you with Intrinsic take it to a much larger If your idea can help maybe even save lives, we can do it on a much larger scale than you could ever Tony Robbins World Renowned Leader Tony Robbins shares his approach to - and how he works with health and wellness founders following the sale of their companies to Want to hear more from Tony? Something went wrong while submitting the READ THE EXCERPT What is your approach to brand building? Hey everybody, itâs Tony My partners here at Intrinsic asked me if I would share what has been my approach to brand building and what advice might I have for somebody who is brand building in the health and wellness I am privileged at this stage to have over We do over $8 billion in business, and Intrinsic is one of those â When I look at any company, a company I am starting, a company I am a partner in, a company that IÂ buy, and I want to grow it, there are three things that I look Number one, do we really know who the ideal client is? You gotta know not who your current client is - who is your ideal Who s the client who s going to buy from you in the middle of winter when the economy shuts down or when COVID happens? Who is the type of customer that s going to love your product so much, they are going to tell everybody else about it? â Number two, you need to come up with an irresistible There are so many businesses that have done Tony Hsieh, whoâs a good friend of mine, he passed away recently, but he took over a little company called Zappoâs. He said I think you should make it so a woman can buy as many shoes as she pairs if she We pay the She tries them on in the comfort of her own And any shoe she doesn t like, for any reason whatsoever, she ships them back and we pay the shipping â This offer took them from a company struggling to survive to literally one of the most powerful rocket ships in They were bought by Amazon for $1.2 â And then the third key is the most important one: Do more for other people than anybody else in the That level of , of service, of caring care, doing more than people expect, builds your How do you differentiate yourself from your competitors? The only way to break through is If I can show the measurable results of the impact of my work, then I could begin to build my brand and begin to reach people on a different So I took on challenges, and thatâs what I encourage businesses to Think of a challenge that your customer or client needs and go solve it for some people, just to build the reputation in the And that s what I I went to the Army and I went to a I said I can take any training in the entire Army, no matter what it I can cut the training time in half and increase the Long story short, I figured it That gave me a different level of confidence, a different level of certainty, but also gave me something I can point That led to business people and that led to turning around And the next thing I know, Iâm working with the President of the United States Bill Clinton and Mother Teresa and Nelson Whenever people fail, they talk about the resources that they were missing: time, energy, money, people, But the most successful people on Earth understand th

Announcing Testcontainers Cloud: Integration Testing has never been easier - AtomicJar, Skip to content AtomicJar, Blog Sign up for early access Menu Technology , Testcontainers Announcing Testcontainers Cloud: Integration Testing has never been easier Let me tell you a When AtomicJar started, our CEO Sergei got himself a shiny new Apple He was eager to start developing the prototype, and of course, as a conscious developer, his first lines of code were followed by an even bigger amount of tests… but that didn’t work! Apparently, the world, or at least one of its subsets in the form of the Docker ecosystem, wasn’t ready for And there are many stories of developers using their own products, but nothing can beat a developer who cannot run their tests! Therefore, ever since then, our focus at AtomicJar has been to make it easy to run tests For ourselves, and, well, a few hundred thousand other developers out This is why we’re excited to announce Testcontainers Cloud! Testcontainers Cloud is the SaaS platform for modern integration testing with real databases, message brokers, cloud services, or any other component of application Built for the existing Testcontainers family of libraries, Testcontainers Cloud brings the same unit experience even to the most constrained development and CI We’re expanding on what development environments are able to use Testcontainers and how teams can use integration tests with the real technologies their applications will use in Let us share more details about Testcontainers Cloud and some feedback we got from the early Welcome Testcontainers Cloud One of the more common approaches to integration testing is running your applications against real instances of databases and other service dependencies locally on developer machines or CI Testcontainers libraries are a popular choice to manage Docker containers with those dependencies and seamlessly integrate them into the tests’ Testcontainers Cloud runs everything that is supported by the Testcontainers library: Cassandra, Cockroach, Couchbase, DB2, MariaDB, MongoDB, MySQL, Neo4j, Oracle Database, PostgreSQL and many other databases using JDBC and R2DBC, as well as modules for popular technologies like Elasticsearch, Kafka, Nginx, RabbitMQ, Solr, Toxiproxy, and Hashicorp While the experience of using integration tests with Testcontainers became almost indistinguishable from unit tests, it imposes various environment restrictions and heavily taxes developer Testcontainer Cloud eliminates all those It runs containers remotely and doesn’t burden the local machine with heavy memory and CPU Instead, Testcontainers Cloud provides plenty of compute power for every container it runs which makes tests snappier to start, faster to execute, and developer workstations more Testcontainers Cloud is fast A typical microservice depends on a few external services, and spinning them up on a single developer workstation or a CI worker machine requires a lot of CPU and On an average developer machine, your Docker installation has access to 2 cores and of memory, which you have to split between all Similarly if you want your laptop not to stall while running a test, you need to severely limit the resources you allocate to the It makes tests slow and the whole experience Testcontainers Cloud uses powerful machines with plenty of resources so your containers start fast and run fast, all while your machine has free resources to run the apps you actually Here’s what developers are saying about their Testcontainers Cloud experience: Testcontainers Cloud shields you from not having a powerful machine, poor internet connection, or not enough space for Docker images and allows you to run fast and repeatable integration tests as a continuous part of your And if you are wondering about the latency – don’t worry, Testcontainers Cloud is closer to you than you think 😉 Testcontainers Cloud is accessible everywhere Testcontainers Cloud is designed to support your existing test suites no matter where you run your Even more – there are various environments where it’s awkward to run Docker workloads! There are continuous integration platforms and solutions that restrict the types of containers that they can run, or require hacky workarounds to allow containers to be run at Or you may not want to your Cloud IDE if you just need to change a couple of lines of ARM based processors are more popular than ever, starting from M1 Macs, to most major cloud providers shifting more and more workloads to these cheaper and more energy efficient compute While it’s possible to run Docker on ARM you are often limited to what images are stable or even available for the ARM Testcontainers Cloud decouples your execution environment from the Docker engine allowing you to effortlessly run your CI jobs no matter what is used to execute them: an ultrabook, Cloud IDEs, Jenkins nodes, Tekton Kubernetes pods, cost efficient ARM build nodes, CI providers that are lacking Docker support and much

Open Source wasmCloud Team About Contact About Us Home About Us Our mission is to revolutionize the way developers build, operate, and mantain distributed Over the last years, new epochs of computing have risen to help developers and enterprises meet the challenges facing their As enterprises raced to digitize their businesses the virtual machine freed us from the constraints of a specific computer, and as orchestrated by the public cloud was adopted and scaled The container freed us from the constraints of a specific Linux environment and as orchestrated by Kubernetes has allowed us to execute workloads across multiple However, today’s developers face new challenges - modern enterprises are now racing to digitize their entire ecosystems from the cloud to the In doing so, enterprises and developers need to adopt a diverse ecosystem of CPUs, increase security, and build applications that can run everywhere - the cloud, browsers, the edge, and on an array of embedded Cosmonic was created to help enterprises rapidly adopt, scale, execute, and operate distributed applications at Compatible with modern Kubernetes and ecosystems, it is not dependent upon them - with Cosmonic you can operate your applications from the cloud to the A stateless, immutable development model enables both dynamic and horizontal Incredibly WebAssembly’s sandboxed, capability model is enhanced through cryptographically enhanced provenance Performant and portable execution with your choice of either JIT’d or interpreted WebAssembly Lattice - a , mesh network provides a unified, flattened topology across any number of disparate environments, clouds, browsers, or From the creators of CNCF wasmCloud . The Argo Project is a suite of open source tools for deploying and running applications and workloads on It uses GitOps paradigms to achieve continuous delivery, progressive delivery and enables MLOps on Argo is a Cloud Native Computing Foundation (CNCF) incubating project and is trusted by leading enterprises around the What is GitOps? GitOps is a set of practices to manage infrastructure and application configurations using a git repository as the source of truth of the desired state of a It is typically coupled with a GitOps operator (such as Argo CD), which automates the delivery of the configuration to the runtime GitOps has gained popularity in recent years because of its workflows and it s natural fit with Kubernetes declarative What is Progressive Delivery? Progresive Delivery, considered the next evolution of continuous delivery, is the practice of incrementally exposing new versions of your application to an initially small subset of users, then gradually larger and larger subset, in order to mitigate the risk of negative impact (e.g. bugs). This is ideally coupled with analysis of key business metrics (e.g. the four golden signals) so that promotions and rollbacks are fully automated and For more on progressive delivery and our approach, watch our KubeCon Â© Akuity, Wolfe Road Sunnyvale, CA Akuity Enterprise Akuity Cloud Resources Company Blog Contact Careers     Akuity - Webb Manifesto Documentation menu You deserve more We believe that there is no such thing as enough privacy in our financial There is only more privacy and less In the Web3 ecosystem, there is certainly not enough Our privacy manifesto We believe that the lack of privacy in the Web3 world is a dire issue that prevents programmable money from becoming more powerful than traditional money This will hinder the impact cryptocurrencies can have on a global Our ecosystem lacks collaborative efforts for privacy creation and suffers from competitive behavior to reduce our own privacy, even under the purported guise of privacy Privacy creation systems today are inefficient because they are not While we have made immeasurable progress in making privacy a relevant topic today, we believe that our collective effort has only solved half the Today when you move your assets across chains, you lose Instead, we should strive for a world where moving your assets contributes to The mechanisms that underpin many successful protocols all function on a locking & unlocking mechanism, a mechanism for privacy We believe users should have privacy wherever they have and move their We create the most privacy by collaborating towards this goal across the entirety of the Web3 protocols and Every new community wants access to liquidity and will engage in highly competitive behaviour to take This is narrowly focused and This is Instead, we are interested in Webb creates a new platform for positive sum, privacy How we actually do An interoperable mixer All your holdings and all your transfers take place in a set of interoperable We scale privacy across the set of bridged chains by obfuscating not just the depositors and withdrawers of assets but also the ecosystems from which these actions take A unified representation for assets We unify your assets in holding and transit under an interoperable webb We do this to grow our anonymity sets as large as Rampant tokenisation has increased the fragmentation of privacy for crypto In a world, unification of assets into common representations will be the biggest contributor to privacy creation across Fully open source All our work is fully open source so that it s clear what goes on underneath the We are fully committed to this vision and will continue to innovate in Outside contributors are welcome! Conductor is an , Apache licensed microservices and workflow orchestration framework Build highly reliable distributed applications using the language of choice Lets us focus on coding the business logic of the application instead of managing complexities of a distributed ecosystem Cleanly decouple the design of the application flow from the implementation Watch this short video to learn more about conductor Why should you use Conductor? Lets you focus on coding the business logic of the application instead of managing the state and complexities of a distributed ecosystem You can cleanly decouple the design of the application flow from the implementation Your application’s resilience is increased with native support in Conductor for retries, error handling and rich metrics You have a powerful visualizations of your application’s execution paths that can shorten debugging times from hours to minutes What can you build with Conductor? Applications composed of distributed microservices or serverless functions Hybrid applications that span across multiple deployment models (e.g. VM deployed monolith, kubernetes deployed containers) Long running workflows that need to wait for days, months or even years between executions (e.g. monthly subscription billing) Mission critical applications with high reliability requirements (e.g. financial transactions Build your first Workflow in 2 Minutes Your First Workflow Java Python Go public TaskResult execute ( Task task ) TaskResult result = new TaskResult ( task ) result . setStatus ( TaskResult . art blocks p r o j e c t s a r t i s t s l e a r n  connect  learn about art blocks what is art blocks?  open Art Blocks is a first of its kind platform focused on genuinely programmable on demand generative content that is stored immutably on the Ethereum You pick a style that you like, pay for the work, and a randomly generated version of the content is created by an algorithm and sent to your Ethereum The resulting piece might be a static image, model, or an interactive Each output is different and there are endless possibilities for the types of content that can be created on the how do i mint?  open If you enjoy the style of a work that is hosted on the Art Blocks platform you can mint a unique iteration for The work is minted generated created on demand so you don t actually know what the specific piece you are getting will look like! To mint, visit a project while connected to If you do not already have Metamask installed you ll need to visit https: metamask.io to install the extension in your Once you re connected, you ll see a purchase button in the description area for each Note that each project has a set maximum iteration limit and if that limit is reached you will be unable to mint a new work! When you click the purchase button you ll be presented with a Metamask window for confirming the It will show the price for the mint as well as the gas cost for executing the Click "Confirm" to initiate the purchase After the transaction is confirmed you will be presented with your generative content! This is a one of a kind iteration generated by the project s The resulting work is represented on the Ethereum network by a token which is a standard ERC721 compatible NFT This means you will instantly be able to see it in your account on various marketplace platforms like OpenSea . Note: If the Ethereum blockchain is backlogged and your token takes too long to mint, you might not be presented with the token image automatically upon minting The token will appear in your "my items" page once the transaction is what is a curated project  open Art Blocks as a platform has established a curation board to carefully select projects for inclusion in the "official" Art Blocks Curated Collection . The intention is to create a collection of works that best represent the vision of the Art Blocks platform, and are released on a schedule allowing collectors to manageably build a significant set of generative The total size and value of these curated drops will be tied to user base to allow newcomers to participate in the experience as the platform The maximum number of full curated sets to exist is tied to the edition size of the smallest drop in that This means there can only ever exist full sets of the set of 6 works and of the current Q1 what is a playground project?  open Artists that have been included in the Curated Collection are then allowed to deploy a project of their choice in the Artist These projects are not "curated" and subsequently are not promoted as an official Art Blocks drop or considered to be part of the "official" Art Blocks To participate, artists must have launched a curated project prior to deploying in the playground and can only have a single ongoing project in the playground at any given Additionally, artists must see the entire project through completion at the initially advertised price and edition size in order to proceed with a subsequent project in the Any adjustments in a project s economics will disqualify the artist from deploying another project in the playground until a subsequent project has been accepted through the curation how does art blocks work? Definition & Process Product Management What Is Product Management? Definition & Process Product management is a core part to any successful That’s why it’s important to know the ins and outs of This article covers: What Is Product Management? Product Management Process : Key Components Best Practices What Is Product Management? Product management is defined as the process of researching user and market needs, designing and building products to meet these needs, determining pricing and marketing strategy, and launching these products to delight It drives continuous innovation and development via an intense focus on the product and its It requires strong business acumen, a deep understanding of UX design, and technical Since product management is an interdisciplinary role, successful product management requires collaboration and alignment between several team members involved in researching, designing, developing, maintaining, marketing, selling, and servicing customers of the Click here to learn more about team Product Management Process: Key Components Product management has been around since the peak of the industrial revolution, with companies producing and marketing thousands of new B2C and B2B products each Most companies making those products started hiring product managers to exclusively manage these products While the products today include an increasing amount of software, the core tenants of managing a product have remained the Below are the universal components and stages of product management lifecycle: Identifying and Assessing Opportunities Product management often starts with identifying new These opportunities come from various sources including external sources like customer requirements, competitor analysis, new market trends, as well as internal sources like ideas from team members across various disciplines and executive It is important to assess these opportunities to see which ones provide the most return on investment considering the customer impact, revenue impact, feasibility (risk), and the effort required . User Research, Market Research and Forecasting Research is critical to make sure the products meet user needs and It is the key to align expectations and estimations with market It also helps understand the market landscape from a demand and competition Market research is not just helpful for product launch, it is key for annual and market forecasting, even after the launch of the It is critical for any product management team to prioritize market analysis as a cornerstone for successful product The role of user research is critical even during the product development phase, right through the product launch Usability studies during and after product launch ensure that the product is indeed meeting customer needs and the product team is able to address potential issues blocking user adoption . Product Vision and Roadmap The art of product management requires coming up with a product vision and roadmap that is both compelling and This requires an understanding of the target customer’s needs as well as the capabilities of the engineering team and the technologies With this understanding, product managers create feature roadmaps across several releases to bring the right product to market at the right Product management is responsible for communicating and evangelizing the product roadmap to the team involved in the product development In order to ensure from various stakeholders , it is important that they understand which features are part of the roadmap and They also provide critical feedback for the effort involved, feasibility analysis and risk assessment for developing various features of the In case of disagreements, it is important to maintain data driven, objective approach and do internal evangelism to rally the team towards a common Product Development Product development is the process of creating the product based on approved designs, features and This includes coordinating work of several disciplines such as UX design , engineering, operations, This also includes managing complexities of the technology stack as well as various between components of the For physical hardware products, this may also require supply chain management and Product management ensures that the actual deadlines and targets are being met across the product team in all This involves continuous communication and coordination across te
